  <h2>Importance of Organic Fertilizers</h2>
  <b>
    Organic fertilizers are derived from natural sources such as plant, animal, and microbial matter. 
    They improve soil health, increase crop productivity sustainably, and reduce dependency on chemical fertilizers. 
    Using organic fertilizers enhances soil structure, microbial activity, and nutrient availability while being environmentally friendly.
  </b>
  <br><br>

  <div class="section">
    <h3>Why Use Organic Fertilizers?</h3>
    <p>
        Organic fertilizers provide essential nutrients to plants and enrich the soil with organic matter. They improve water retention, reduce soil erosion, and promote sustainable agriculture practices. 
        They are safe for the environment and help maintain ecological balance.
    </p>
    <br>
    <b>Benefits of Organic Fertilizers</b>
    <ul>
      <li>Improved soil fertility and structure</li>
      <li>Enhanced microbial activity in soil</li>
      <li>Reduced chemical dependency</li>
      <li>Better water retention in soil</li>
      <li>Safe for humans, animals, and the environment</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h3>Types of Organic Fertilizers</h3>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th>Source</th>
        <th>Uses</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Compost</td>
        <td>Decomposed organic waste</td>
        <td>Improves soil structure and fertility</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Manure</td>
        <td>Animal dung (cow, horse, poultry)</td>
        <td>Provides essential nutrients and organic matter</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Green Manure</td>
        <td>Leguminous plants</td>
        <td>Enriches soil nitrogen and organic content</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Biofertilizers</td>
        <td>Microorganisms like Rhizobium, Azotobacter</td>
        <td>Enhances nutrient availability naturally</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h3>How to Apply Organic Fertilizers?</h3>
    <p>
        Organic fertilizers can be applied before sowing, during growth, or as top dressing. Proper application ensures plants receive essential nutrients efficiently.
        Incorporating organic matter into the soil enhances fertility and provides long-term benefits.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Apply compost evenly before planting</li>
      <li>Use manure or green manure as soil amendment</li>
      <li>Biofertilizers can be mixed with seeds or soil</li>
      <li>Regular monitoring ensures balanced nutrient supply</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

